B)=25.5 (24.8) at large angular separations. For the brighter sources we\nhave measured the half-light radius and the n parameter of the best-fit\ndeconvolved Sersic-law surface-brightness profile, and the ellipticity and\norientation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 2 May 2001 17:08:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-06"}
